<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
"Personaly I disaprove of quad kiting becuase it puts other players in danger when the quad kiter looses controle."<P>lol...ok.  I've never killed anyone while quad kiting.  It's very easy to do quad kiting safely but I won't get into this with you right now.<P>In any event, don't believe it when they tell you that quad kiting was an unexpected result of the use of snare and aoe spells.  I could buy this for druids since they gave them single target snare spells, but they gave us aoe snares long after the idea of quadkiting was invented.  They had to see that wizards would be doing the same thing.<P>As for AoE in dugneons...<BR>Verant has very mixed feelings about aoe.  On the one hand, they have explicitly encouraged us to use aoe tactics (yes, they actually have).  However, their policies regarding zone disruption and their lack of forthought in zone design make the tactic unusable (on paper at least).  As a solution, they should build dungeons that are specifically oriented towards aoe tactics.  The current dungeons aren't well suited to it and basically force aoe groups to disrupt others.  In any event, they cannot tell you that you cannot use aoe.  They can only tell you to restrict its use in such a way that makes it far less desirable than it's potential allows for.<P>--------------------<P>Bethude<BR>59 Evoker
