Actually, neither kiting nor fear kiting were intended by Verant either.  Kiting, fear kiting, and quad kiting were all invented by ingenious players.  There are more than a third of a million people playing this game.  It stands to reason those third of a million people will think of some techniques the developers had not intended.  Does this make them wrong?  Yes and no.  If you are exploiting the game (example: If you find a ledge where you can kill monsters and they can not attack back), then it is wrong.  If you are not exploiting the game, but using all you have to your advantage (example: kiting, fear kiting and quad kiting), then it is not wrong.<P>There will be some people jealous people that want you stopped, because you get more experience than they get.  There will be some people (like me) that look at quad kiting and say, "If you have the guts to try it, then you deserve the exp, but this is not foe me."  There will be other people that try it and like it.<P>From what I understand, there are limited areas in the game that are conducive to quad kiting.  My suggestion to the people that do not like quad kiting - Don't go to those places.  You will not even know it is going on.  I have been in the game for some time.  I have heard of quad kiting, but I have never even seen anyone attempt it.<P>--------------------<P>Cheers,<BR> - Daemonn Venator 56th level wizard<BR> - Roghan 50th level paladin
